The President of the United States and the Prime Minister of Bulgaria have reaffirmed the strong friendship and alliance between their two countries. They aim to deepen security cooperation and promote economic growth and prosperity. The United States commends Bulgaria's commitment to burden-sharing and exceeding defense spending targets. The two countries plan to strengthen defense technology and industry partnerships. They also emphasize the importance of energy security and diversification of energy sources. Bulgaria aspires to become a regional natural gas hub and enhance its energy security. They also intend to work together through multilateral fora to promote regional development. The United States supports Bulgaria's efforts to defend its independence and sovereignty from malign influence. They stress the importance of good governance, the rule of law, and addressing corruption. The two countries also highlight their trade and investment ties and commit to fair treatment of investors and expanding bilateral trade. They plan to conduct regular strategic dialogues in the future.